# gen81: priority operators + "but"/"ma" negation.
# "but": second sub-turn overrides; only the second is answered.
# First make cat and gatto known predicates so closed-world "No." applies.
> felix is a cat
< Learned: cat(felix).
> rex is a dog but is rex a cat?
< No.
# "ma" (Italian but): the correction wins.
> felix è un gatto
< Learned: gatto(felix).
> rex è un cane ma è rex un gatto?
< No.
# Compound with expanded starters: "dimmi" triggers split.
> dimmi chi sei e cosa sai fare?
< I am parrot0. I can answer questions about facts and rules, do simple arithmetic, reason about cause and effect, compare quantities, tell whether two things are the same, remember things you tell me, read a short passage and pull out facts, track what a pronoun refers to, continue a sequence you teach me, remember what we talked about.
